Appointment Setting: Bridging the Gap Between Marketing and Revenue
One of the most direct paths from demand generation to revenue is a well-executed appointment setting program. In 2026, AI has made appointment setting smarter, faster, and far more efficient than the traditional SDR-heavy model.

AI-powered appointment setting combines intent data to identify the warmest prospects, automated outreach to initiate engagement across multiple channels, and human SDRs to handle conversations once initial interest has been established. This hybrid model reduces the cost per qualified meeting while improving the quality of conversations that actually make it onto the calendar.

For B2B companies targeting the US market, appointment setting programs that integrate with CRM systems in real time, provide detailed notes on prospect behavior and interests, and deliver contacts who have been nurtured to a point of genuine readiness are a significant step up from the traditional cold outreach model.

